    "extras": [
      "Bran Castle is best treated as a Brasov day trip rather than a luggage-hauling transfer stop; buses are cheap and frequent enough for a relaxed out-and-back day.",
      "If you want to use the research-backed Sighișoara stop, break the Sibiu to Cluj-Napoca journey there for the Clock Tower, Vlad Dracul House, and Citadel Square before continuing north.",
      "Vegetarian travelers should look for fasting-menu or “post” dishes: mămăligă with cheese, mushroom stews, zacuscă, vegetable ciorbă, and cheese pastries are easy wins across Romania.",
      "Use Bolt or Uber instead of hailing street taxis in Bucharest, and keep around ₹3,600–₹5,400 worth of RON cash for small museums, bus tickets, and village stops.",
      "May–June and September are the easiest months for this route, with milder weather and lower crowd pressure around Bran Castle and the Brasov-Sibiu corridor."
